Overall - Great Food and Great Customer Service  LOCATION - Note: This Five Guys is located within the metro "underground" area between HUD and USPS. It's not at the main street level.  The first time I came here, Five Guys forgot to add sauce to my burger. I returned to my desk disappointed and ate my burger as is. I submitted a survey and mentioned my experience.  Within two days, the store owner contacted me with his apologies, offered me a gift card, and invited me to return. I returned and was met with friendly staff (again) and received a complimentary meal. The store owner shocked me with his 100% dedication to customer service. I now go to this Five Guys at least once a week.  I've returned at least 3 times and my order has never been wrong.

This Five Guys has always been slow, but recently the customer service has started to suck on top of that. I order a pretty uncomplicated burger (ketchup, mustard, mayo) and wind up with lettuce, pickles, and mushrooms? Are you high or something? If this was a one-time event I might write it off, but the fact is this has been occurring fairly consistently for a couple months now.  This Five Guy's has always existed almost exclusively to prey on tourists who don't know any better, and since I work nearby I could deal with that. But if I'm spending $13 for a burger, small fries, and drink, they should damn well be able to figure out what ketchup and mustard are.  TL;DR they screw up your orders, don't waste your time.
